Last week, @realDonaldTrump came to #LA with promises to address homelessness.

It was BS.

All his administration did was cut funding & threaten vulnerable communities.

That‚Äôs why @RepKatieHill, myself & #CA‚Äôs congressional delegation wrote to POTUS demanding meaningful action. https://t.co/1UNl37Oy3g

full_text:
I‚Äôve spent my career working to end homelessness and I‚Äôve transitioned thousands of families and veterans off the streets into permanent, affordable housing.

Thank you to my CA colleagues for your dedication to solving this crisis, as well as @SenFeinstein & @SenKamalaHarris. https://t.co/lwGZXIDT9I

1/ Today we mark 50 years since the #Stonewall Riots, a seminal moment in the LGBTQ movement when patrons of the New York City bar rioted against oppression & brutality.

The Stonewall Riots ignited the modern LGBTQ rights movement & harnessed the political power of LGBTQ people. https://t.co/wseUejjdzk

full_text: We don't always teach LGBT history in schools, but the Stonewall riot was not the first or last fight for LGBT rights. Knowing our history is key to preventing it from becoming our future. https://t.co/Q5eeTK9x1L

Today we're passing the #DreamAct.

What the bill does: 
-Provides permanent protections for #Dreamers, who have only ever called America home, and people who came here fleeing violence or natural disaster

What the bill doesn't do: 
-Open our borders to drugs and crime

full_text:
When I worked in social services, I saw the trauma that children who were separated from their families went through. We have given #DOJ, #HHS, & #DHS months to turn around docs on where these kids are ‚Äî every single day that passes we deepen their trauma.
